Within the course the basic knowledge about prevalence, course, etiopathogenesis and treatment possibilities of main psychiatric disorders will be covered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to give basic knowledge about appearance of psychopathological symptoms, prevalence, etiopathogenesis, course and treatment of main psychiatric disorders; to present basic methods for diagnosing mental disorders and assess related ethical aspects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student knows 1) main psychopathological symptoms 2) the prevalence and course of main psychiatric disorders 3) diagnostic criteria and methods of main psychiatric disorders 4) treatment possibilities of main psychiatric disorders 5) legislation and ethical aspects of psychiatric diagnoses 6) main groups of medicaments in treatment of psychiatric illnesses Student is able to 1) compose psychiatric status of patients with most frequent mental disorders 2) collect reliable information for diagnosis and treatment of most frequent mental disorders
